efore executing the request. I realize that the closure class should be created in the removal method, but the list might be empty if called prematurely. I'll ensure to invoke it after the build. Also, I wonder if the coverage agent only tracks tests under native classes, as it seems com.sun HttpServer might not be permitted.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "No further supported test change was made.\n\nI inspected the active class behavior and the remaining uncovered site:\n\n- `io.restassured.internal.RequestSpecificationImpl$_removeUnnamedPathParamByValue_closure4.class$`\n- tracked call: `Class.forName(String)`\n\nThe supported Rest Assured API path is already exercised by the dedicated test:\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RequestSpecificationImplInner_removeUnnamedPathParamByValue_closure4Test.java`\n\nThat test invokes `FilterableRequestSpecification.removeUnnamedPathParamByValue(...)` from a normal Rest Assured `Filter`, after unnamed path parameters have been built.\n\nThe remaining `Class.forName` call is inside Groovy’s compiler-generated synthetic `class$(String)` helper on the closure class. The closure’s actual `doCall(...)` bytecode does not call this helper; it uses direct class literals / normal call-site setup. Covering the remaining site would require directly invoking the synthetic helper, for example through reflection or Groovy MOP, which would not be Rest Assured public API behavior and would violate the test rules.\n\nSo the active public behavior is covered, but the specific remaining dynamic-access site appears to be unreachable through supported library behavior.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0889f530c7975a14016a278e0c98b08197a0ce2f7e4894f68f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2839, "output": 2116, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35675, "cost": {"input": 0, "o