[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Refining test coverage**\n\nI’m considering refining the existing test to ensure there's coverage for the Direct public API. Maybe I need to create a test file that matches the existing one-to-one structure. I wonder if the file name, like Inner_remove, is causing confusion. There might be an issue where our test didn’t actually invoke the remove function due to filter executions. \n\nI think I should add a test that checks the closure-generated getter, but I’m unsure about exposing it through exceptions.\n\n**Evaluating test cases**\n\nI'm thinking about whether it's okay to focus on just the active class and the tests under target. Maybe I should add comments, but then again, they might be unnecessary. I wonder if I've created a duplicate with an existing test that's already calling a method but isn't dedicated. There's confusion because previous tests are incorrectly calling methods in the wrong class. I need to ensure everything's correctly covered, especially around public methods and any duplicate scenarios. I'll check the test results to confirm proper execution.\n\n**Refining test setup**\n\nI'm considering using the existing file name exactly as it maps to the active class name, which involves replacing the dollar sign with \"Inner\" for a more straightforward naming convention. Next, I think it might be beneficial to alter the test to call a method before executing the request. I realize that the closure class should be created in the removal method, but the list might be empty if called prematurely. I'll ensure to invoke it after the build. Also, I wonder if the coverage agent only tracks tests under native classes, as it seems com.sun HttpServer might not be permitted.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0889f530c7975a14016a278de5ac6c81978d4e7ae7184bd75a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ44M4m6dVlJCXpBFF--ii